sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1283002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We construct a biological system that produces a wintergreen odor and protective melittin under extensive UV radiation. The biological system includes two generators: the UV-responsing wintergreen odor generator (BBa_K994000) and the protective melittin generator(BBa_K1283000). It not only can warn people of intense UV irradiation by a wintergreen odor, but also produce protective melittin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hongmei Du
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From iGEM registry and academic paper

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: UV-WG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The UV-responsive wintergreen odor generator catalyzes the conversion of the precursor salicylic acid to the wintergreen odor methyl salicylate under extensive UV irradiation. The biosynthetic device is composed of two transcriptional devices: Rec A (SOS) promoter (BBa_J22106) and a wintergreen odor enzyme generator (BBa_J45119). The odor generator takes as input extensive UV irradiation and produce as output an enzyme that catalyzes production of an odor from a chemical precursor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1283000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The protective melittin generator is composed of two transcriptional devices: RecA (SOS) promoter (BBa_J22106) and synthesized melittin gene with enterokinase digested sequence. The protective generator takes as input extensive UV radiation and produces as output fusion melittin. Melittin can improve immunity and scavenging free radicals to alleviate the harm from electromagnetic radiation, such as blue light and UV.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hongmei Du
